  "text": "The aim of subsequent therapy was to sustain remission in patients who had achieved CR. If there were some abnormalities in certain parameters but the patient had not met the definition of relapse [CITATION_1] , the following treatment strategies might be considered: 1. continue the continuation therapy; 2. prolong the intervals between every cycle of treatment described in the continuation therapy protocol; or 3. administer prednisone only in the minimum effective dose.",
